PEOPLE, Respondent, v. DOXTATER, Appellant. (Supreme Court, General Term, Fourth Department. May 18, 1894.) Action by the people against Milton W. Doxtater.

Argued before HARDIN, P. J., and MARTIN and MERWIN, JJ.

No opinion. Motion for leave to appeal to the court of appeals granted on the ground that a question of law is involved which ought to be reviewed by that court. See 27 N. Y. Supp. 481.
